SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 697
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the University of
Tennessee men's rugby team on winning the
2025 National Collegiate Rugby Division 1-AA
National Championship.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful collegiate athletic teams that, through their magnificent exploits,
bring honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the University of Tennessee (UT) men's rugby team achieved an
extraordinary level of success during the 2025 season, culminating in their second National
Collegiate Rugby Division 1-AA National Championship; and
WHEREAS, the men of UT rugby won their first national title in 2021; and
WHEREAS, with two minutes remaining in the 2025 title game, the Vols reached the try
zone to provide the winning score, besting Bowling Green 21-15 to claim the team's second
national championship; and
WHEREAS, hailed as "true Volunteers on and off the pitch," the UT men's rugby players
have long demonstrated their commitment to community service by assisting the Friends of the
Great Smoky Mountains National Park with the organization's fundraising activities; and
WHEREAS, national championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication,
and the ability to work together as a team and excel with a cooperative spirit; the Vols exhibited
each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
WHEREAS, the University of Tennessee men's rugby players epitomize all that is good
in today's student athletes, as they have achieved the highest level of success on the pitch
while showing the highest degree of character in all their endeavors; and
SJR0697
012861
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the dedication, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of young
men not only made possible a national championship but also surely bode well for their future
success; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the men's rugby players
of the University of Tennessee for serving as exemplars of the high quality of Tennessee's
college students; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the coaches and players
of the University of Tennessee men's rugby team for capturing their second national title by
winning the 2025 National Collegiate Rugby Division 1-AA National Championship, thus
continuing the Volunteers' proud tradition of success both on and off the field of play.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
